.SH NAME
\*LSgFileSelectionBoxReplaceSuffix \*O\(em A FileSelectionBox function used to 
replace the suffix of the current file name.
.iX "SgFileSelectionBoxReplaceSuffix"
.iX "FileSelectionBox functions" "SgFileSelectionBoxReplaceSuffix"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sS
.iS
\&#include <Xm/FileSB.h>
.sp \n(PDu
void SgFileSelectionBoxReplaceSuffix (\*Vwidget, file_type, default_suffix\*L)
.ta .5i 1.5i
	Widget	\*Vwidget\*L;
	const char *	\*Vfile_type\*L;
	const char *	\*Vdefault_suffix\*L;
.wH .fi
.iE
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
\*LSgFileSelectionReplaceSuffix\*O is used to replace the suffix of
the current filename within a FileSelectionBox.  The parameters given
to the function are the FileSelectionBox widget, the FTR file type
from which to derive the new suffix, and a default suffix to be used
if the FTR database does not contain a suffix for the given file type.
.VL .75i 
.LI "\*Vwidget\*O"
Specifies the FileSelectionBox widget ID.
.LI "\*Vfile_type\*O"
Specifies the FTR file type to be used in determining the new suffix.
.LI "\*Vdefault_suffix\*O"
Specifies the suffix to be used if FTR database does not contain a
suffix for the given file type.
.LE
.PP 
For a complete definition of FileSelectionBox and its associated resources, see
\*LSgFileSelectionBox(3X)\*O.
.LE 
